  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "`shap` does not list `matplotlib` as a requirement, and installing `shap` via `pip` will not also install `matplotlib` if it is not already installed. However, shap/shap/plots/colors/_colors.py imports `matplotlib`:\r\n\r\n    try:\r\n        import matplotlib\r\n        from matplotlib.colors import LinearSegmentedColormap\r\n\r\nAnd does nothing if matplotlib is not installed:\r\n\r\n    except ImportError:\r\n        pass\r\n\r\nTherefore, when trying to plot any shap plot, an error occurs if the environment does not have `matplotlib` installed.",
